   289	    """Parse a `setFormat raw` sample output file.
   290	
   291	    Supports common variants:
   292	    - 3D coord rows: `x y z v0 [v1 v2 ...]` (typical for type=points output)
   293	    - Distance-column rows: `distance v0 [v1 v2 ...]` (type=uniform / type=sets with axis)
   294	
   295	    Returns a list of (coords_tuple, values_tuple). Callers reconcile
   296	    coord shape (3 for xyz, 1 for distance).
   297	
   298	    Rules:
   299	    - Lines starting with `#` are skipped (comments).
   300	    - Empty lines are skipped.
   301	    - Lines that don't parse as all-float are skipped.
   302	    - Lines with exactly 3 floats are treated as distance + 2 field values
   303	      (unusual case), not x/y/z.
   304	    - Lines with ≥4 floats: first 3 are (x, y, z), remainder are values.
   305	    """
   306	    result: List[Tuple[Tuple[float, ...], Tuple[float, ...]]] = []
   307	    for raw_line in text.splitlines():
   308	        line = raw_line.strip()
   309	        if not line or line.startswith("#"):
   310	            continue
   311	        parts = line.split()
   312	        try:
   313	            floats = [float(p) for p in parts]
   314	        except ValueError:
   315	            continue
   316	        if len(floats) >= 4:
   317	            coords = tuple(floats[:3])
   318	            values = tuple(floats[3:])
   319	        elif len(floats) >= 2:
   320	            coords = (floats[0],)
   321	            values = tuple(floats[1:])
   322	        else:
   323	            continue
   324	        result.append((coords, values))
   325	    return result
