+# DEC-V61-049 Pilot — lid_driven_cavity novice walk
+
+## Persona check
+- I am reviewing this as a first-semester CFD graduate student, not as a mature CFD validation reviewer. I know the incompressible Navier-Stokes equations at the textbook level, have read the early Anderson CFD chapters, and have run OpenFOAM's `icoFoam/cavity` tutorial once. I recognize words like SIMPLE, PISO, `blockMesh`, `checkMesh`, `sampleDict`, Re, residuals, and centerline profiles, but I do not yet have reliable intuition for SIMPLE under-relaxation, GCI/Richardson extrapolation, stream-function post-processing, or how to defend a validation report against published data. My concrete goal is: can `/learn/lid_driven_cavity` teach me enough to reproduce the case, diagnose obvious failures, post-process the result, compare against Ghia 1982 in at least five meaningful ways, and write a 1000-word course report without inventing missing facts? On the current page, my answer is no.
+
+## Step 1 findings — Reading the page
+- 🟠 **Hero / physics bullets** — The page starts cleanly: square cavity, moving lid, no-slip walls, Re definition are all visible in the LDC entry (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:122-135`) and rendered in the Story tab (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:340-350`). My confusion is not the physical setup; it is the missing "from textbook to OpenFOAM" bridge. As a novice I still do not know the actual coordinate scale, whether the page wants a unit square or `convertToMeters 0.1`, and whether Re=100 is achieved by `nu=0.01` or `nu=0.001`. The backend generator uses `convertToMeters 0.1` and `nu=0.1/Re`, so Re=100 gives `nu=0.001` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:756-782`), while the workflow says `nu=0.01` for a 1x1 cavity (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:146`). Fix: show a boxed "dimensionless tutorial path" and "harness audit path" table, or pick one path and keep all commands consistent.
+- 🟠 **Why validation matters** — The validation paragraph says Ghia 1982's 129x129 data is the gold standard and centerline matching decides whether the first CFD pass succeeded (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:135`). That is motivating, but as a student I immediately ask: what exact table, what axis, how many points, and what error norm? Those details are scattered later and partially conflict: the gold YAML says u_centerline is Table I interpolated to 17 y points (`knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:59-97`), the page's observable card says "Table II" for u_centerline (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:141`), and the public flow-field caption says Table I has both u and v profiles (`ui/frontend/src/data/flowFields.ts:21-24`). Fix: one mini "Ghia data map" should state: Table I = u(x=0.5,y), Table II = v(x,y=0.5), current harness compares only u.
+- 🟠 **Physics intuition** — The three new paragraphs are valuable but too compressed for my level. Terms like "Taylor-Görtler 螺旋涡", "weak turbulence regime", "2D 稳态解仍然数学存在但实验里看到的是时均场", "benchmark protocol" appear in one block (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:136`). I can appreciate the story, but I do not know what the stream function is, how vortex center is measured, or why 2D mathematical steady state can coexist with 3D experimental unsteadiness. Fix: add a short glossary under this block for `primary vortex`, `secondary vortex`, `stream function ψ`, `steady 2D idealization`, and `Ghia table`.
+- 🔴 **Common pitfall** — The pitfall says lid corner velocity singularity can cause divergence and suggests mesh refinement, relaxed residual criteria, or accepting small corner error (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:137`). I do not know how much residual relaxation is acceptable before the validation becomes dishonest. The troubleshooting later says residuals should drop below `1e-5` (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:147`), while the pitfall says "放宽残差判据" without a safe floor. Fix: say "do not loosen below X for report runs; if you loosen for exploration, label the run non-validation."
+- 🔴 **Solver card** — The solver card assumes I understand SIMPLE, pressure correction, URF, GAMG, residual control, and `linearUpwind` in one paragraph (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:138`). Worse, it states `U≈0.7, p≈0.3`, but the actual generator writes `U 0.9` and `p 0.3` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:992-1001`). It also says `fvSchemes` uses `linearUpwind`, but the current generator uses `bounded Gauss limitedLinearV 1` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:907-912`). Fix: align the prose with the actual emitted case files, then add a "why these values are safe at Re=100" note.
+- 🔴 **Mesh card** — The page says `ncx=ncy=40` is enough for the teaching run and the workflow repeats `(40 40 1)` (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:139`, `ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:144`), but the actual LDC generator emits `(129 129 1)` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:6826-6829`), the rendered contour title says 129x129, and the gold YAML marks 129x129 as the mesh info (`knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:98-103`). This is a blocker for reproduction because I do not know which grid my report is supposed to reproduce. Fix: choose "audit run = 129x129" as the primary path; keep 40x40 only as a labeled quick exploratory run.
+- 🔴 **Boundary-condition card** — The text names patches `movingWall`, `fixedWalls`, and `referencePressure` (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:140`), but the current generator names patches `lid`, `wall1`, `wall2`, `bottom`, `frontAndBack` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:6835-6865`) and writes `pRefCell/pRefValue` in the `SIMPLE` block (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:979-990`). The workflow also tells me to edit `0/U` with `movingWall` and `fixedWalls` (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:146`), which will not match the actual `blockMeshDict` if I copy the generator. Fix: publish one complete set of dictionaries, or at least keep patch names identical across prose, runbook, and generator.
+- 🔴 **Observable extraction card** — This is the highest-risk narrative block. It says u_centerline is Ghia Table II and v_centerline is Table I, and says the case "also supports" v_centerline plus primary vortex as cross-validation (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:141`). The gold YAML says the opposite for u and explicitly warns that v_centerline and primary_vortex_location are not corrected and not exercised by the current audit comparator (`knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:26-32`, `knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:47-56`). As a novice, I would trust the page and write a false report claiming three validation channels exist. Fix: replace the card with an honest state: current automated comparison = u_centerline only; v_centerline and vortex center are planned but blocked by gold/reference cleanup.
+- 🟠 **Benchmark lineage** — The lineage block is useful and names Burggraf, Ghia, Botella-Peyret, and Shankar-Deshpande (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:157-164`). The missing novice bridge is "which line of my report uses which source?" I need a short mapping: Ghia for centerline values, Burggraf for historical context, Botella-Peyret for high-accuracy follow-up, Shankar-Deshpande for broader flow physics. Fix: add "how to cite in your report" bullets.
+- 🔴 **Reproducibility and troubleshooting blocks** — The component renders the workflow as if it is "complete command/file sequence" (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:528-550`), but the LDC data only gives high-level editing instructions and omits complete file contents (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:142-149`). Troubleshooting is helpful for residuals, mesh, overshoot, pressure reference, and missing secondary vortices (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:150-155`), but it depends on observables the current page does not teach me to compute, especially primary vortex location and secondary-vortex visibility. Fix: include a copy-paste minimal case or a generated reference bundle that contains the exact dictionaries.
+
+## Step 2 findings — Reproducibility walk
+- **Step 1: 准备 case 骨架** — Command shown: `foamNewCase ldc_re100 && cd ldc_re100` (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:143`). I cannot trust this as a pasteable command. My OpenFOAM tutorial experience used copying `$FOAM_TUTORIALS/incompressible/icoFoam/cavity/cavity`; I do not know whether `foamNewCase` exists in my OpenFOAM version. The detail says "从 ... icoFoam/cavity 拷贝模板" but the command does not copy anything. Also the page has already switched to `simpleFoam`, so starting from an `icoFoam` tutorial needs explicit changes to `controlDict`, `fvSchemes`, and `fvSolution`. Fix: give a tested command sequence, e.g. copy the tutorial or download the harness reference case, then list every file to change.
+- **Step 2: 写 blockMeshDict** — Command shown: `$EDITOR system/blockMeshDict` (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:144`). I cannot execute the step without inventing the full dictionary. The line says vertices `(0 0 0)-(1 1 0.1)`, cells `(40 40 1)`, patches `movingWall/fixedWalls/frontAndBack`. The actual generator uses `convertToMeters 0.1`, cells `(129 129 1)`, and patches `lid/wall1/wall2/bottom/frontAndBack` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:6812-6865`). Fix: embed the full `blockMeshDict` or link the exact generated file.
+- **Step 3: 生成网格** — Command shown: `blockMesh` (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:145`). This is executable, but the expected artifact is wrong for the audit path: it says `nCells=1600`, while the actual generated mesh is 129x129x1 = 16641 cells (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:6826-6829`, `knowledge/gold_standards/lid_driven_cavity.yaml:98-103`). It also says "用 checkMesh" but does not include the command or pass criteria. Fix: add `checkMesh | tee log.checkMesh`, expected `Mesh OK`, expected cell count, and known acceptable warnings.
+- **Step 4: 设置 BC 与 Re** — No command is shown (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:146`). This is not runnable for a novice because I need the full `0/U`, `0/p`, and properties file. It says `constant/transportProperties` and `nu=0.01`; the actual generator writes `constant/physicalProperties` and computes `nu=0.001` because the physical length is 0.1 m (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:756-782`). It says `movingWall` and `fixedWalls`; actual `0/U` uses `lid`, `wall1`, `wall2`, `bottom`, `frontAndBack` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:1009-1059`). Fix: put the full dictionaries on the page or in the reference zip.
+- **Step 5: 启动 solver** — Command shown: `simpleFoam > log.simpleFoam &` (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:147`). This is close to executable, but it omits `foamLog log.simpleFoam`, how to stop/wait for completion, and how to know the final time was written. The detail says `writeInterval=500`; current generator writes `writeInterval 2000` in `controlDict` for fields (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:844-850`) and Phase 7 sample function writes every 500 iterations (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:701-727`). Fix: distinguish field write interval from sample write interval and give expected files after iteration 1000/2000.
+- **Step 6: 抽取 u-centerline** — Command shown: `postProcess -func sampleDict` (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:148`). I do not know if this is correct for the current OpenFOAM setup because the generator embeds a `functions { sample { type sets; ... } }` block in `controlDict` (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:698-741`) and separately writes `system/sampleDict` for gold-anchored point sampling (`src/foam_agent_adapter.py:1116-1132`). The run artifacts show files like `sample/1000/uCenterline.xy`, not `postProcessing/sampleDict/<t>/line_x05_U.xy` as the page claims. Fix: specify the exact expected path, columns, coordinate normalization, and the command that generated it for this repo's OpenFOAM version.
+
+## Step 3 findings — Gold comparison, 5-dimension check
+
+Current strict Compare tab count: **1 visible scalar dimension**. `CompareTab` renders one gold stat block, one measured stat block, and one tolerance band from `ValidationReport.gold_standard`/`measurement` (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:897-945`). It does not render a profile, v-centerline, vortex location, stream-function extrema, kinetic energy, wall shear, or a grid-convergence plot. Across the whole `/learn` page, the Story tab embeds a scientific report iframe for LDC (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:1840-1919`) and the Mesh tab shows a convergence slider (`ui/frontend/src/pages/learn/LearnCaseDetailPage.tsx:1073-1230`), so the student can see more evidence outside Compare. But for independent gold-comparison dimensions, I count **at most 2 across the full page**: u_centerline profile and a grid-convergence trend on one u_centerline sample. Derived metrics such as L2, L∞, RMS, max deviation, and pass count are useful statistics, but they are not independent physics observables.
