+## Step 5 — Novice report stub
+Using only the current `/learn/lid_driven_cavity` page, I would write the following report stub:
+
+The lid-driven cavity is a canonical two-dimensional incompressible Navier-Stokes benchmark. The geometry is a square cavity. The top wall moves to the right with nondimensional velocity \(U=1\), while the other three walls are no-slip. The Reynolds number is defined as \(Re=UL/\nu\), and the page focuses on Re=100. At this Reynolds number the flow is laminar and steady, so the page recommends `simpleFoam`, a steady SIMPLE solver, instead of a transient PISO/PIMPLE run. The main physical picture is that the moving lid drags the upper fluid layer to the right, viscosity transfers momentum downward, and the closed side and bottom walls force the flow to recirculate. This creates a large clockwise primary vortex and small counter-rotating secondary vortices near the lower corners.
+
+For validation, the page uses Ghia, Ghia & Shin 1982 as the gold standard. The primary observable is the horizontal velocity along the vertical centerline \(x=0.5\). The simulated \(u/U_{lid}\) profile should be compared to Ghia's tabulated values at multiple \(y/L\) locations. The page says the comparison is important because matching this profile is the first proof that the solver, mesh, boundary conditions, and extraction path are reasonable. The real OpenFOAM report shows a contour with streamlines, a centerline profile plot, a pointwise deviation plot, and a residual convergence plot. The residuals decay to around \(10^{-5}\), so the numerical iteration appears converged. The profile plot indicates that many Ghia points are close, but the pointwise deviation plot reports only 11/17 points inside the 5% tolerance. Therefore I would describe the current result as partially matching Ghia, not a clean validation pass.
+
+【I don't know】The page does not give me a complete `blockMeshDict`, `0/U`, `0/p`, `fvSchemes`, or `fvSolution`, so I cannot reproduce the run from the page without inventing files. 【I don't know】The workflow says 40x40 cells and `nu=0.01`, but the report figure says 129x129 and the generator uses `convertToMeters 0.1` with `nu=0.001`; I do not know which setup belongs in my course report. 【I don't know】The observable card says v-centerline and primary-vortex location are supported, but the current Compare tab only gives me one scalar tolerance band and the gold YAML warns that v-centerline and vortex center are not corrected. I cannot honestly claim five validation dimensions. 【Page doesn't say】I do not know how to compute the stream function, vortex strength, secondary vortex positions, integrated kinetic energy, or wall shear stress. 【Page doesn't say】I do not know how to cite the synthetic stream-function image versus the real OpenFOAM contour, or why the synthetic picture looks more symmetric than the real contour. Because of these gaps, the report can describe the physical story and one u-centerline comparison, but it cannot yet be a full reproducibility/validation report.
+
