+- 🟠 **Fix the scalar/profile split-brain.** `ValidationReport` already has `profile_verdict` fields (`ui/backend/schemas/validation.py:253-276`) and backend computes 11/17 profile status (`ui/backend/services/validation_report.py:929-997`), but Compare tab does not surface that split. Add "scalar anchor verdict" vs "profile verdict" labels so the student does not read a single PASS/FAIL as the whole profile truth.
+- 🟡 **Make report-writing guidance explicit.** After benchmark lineage (`ui/frontend/src/data/learnCases.ts:157-164`), add "what to write in your report" bullets: geometry/BC, solver/mesh, convergence evidence, u-profile comparison, known limitations, and not-yet-supported dimensions.
+- 🟡 **Normalize paths in docs and UI copy.** The prompt path `reports/lid_driven_cavity/phase5_renders/` is stale; actual files live under `reports/phase5_renders/lid_driven_cavity/...`. Use the actual path in future review prompts and any downloadable reproduction README.
+
+## Overall pilot verdict
+- Current reading value for a novice trying to reproduce and write a course report: **4/10**.
+- It would rise to **8/10** if these are fixed: one authoritative copy-paste run path; complete OpenFOAM dictionaries; honest u-only comparison state; Compare tab with at least five independent validation dimensions; corrected v/vortex gold; annotated contour with real-vs-synthetic distinction; a glossary for SIMPLE/URF/GCI/stream function; and report-writing prompts that tell the student exactly what claims are supported.
+- Is "just fix LDC and roll to 9 others" feasible? **Partly, but the gap is structural.** LDC is the easiest case, and it already exposes the structural problem: the content layer, gold YAML, backend comparator, static reference images, live render path, and Compare tab are not a single coherent learning contract. A per-case content patch will help, but rolling to the other 9 should not happen until the LDC pilot establishes a reusable pattern: supported-observable table, copy-paste runbook, five-dimension comparison model, render annotation standard, and explicit "not implemented yet" labels. Otherwise the other cases will inherit the same one-scalar validation problem with more complicated physics.

